node.text:
Spent the week here in Minnesota building the track for round two of the championship. Amazing working with @andrewcarlson15 and crew. The track has so much elevation change, huge banks and zer-gravity drops. It’s windy and going to race really well. Almost no dust and great dirt here but we are intentionally not watering a few of the corners to see if the swept line could be a potential solution for other tracks where the soil blue grooves right away. Happy to get some laps on the CanAm to confirm the jumps are super smooth and will be easy on the cars.
@scott_speed @nitrocircus @yokohamatire @redbullmotorsports

node.text:
Tire changing practice.. like a NASCAR pit stop but completely different 😂 @newenglandforestrally is known for its high attrition rate. Lots of “gotcha’s” and big rocks on the sides of the roads as well as big jumps like @rallyfinland so @rhianongelsomino and I figured it was worth doing a few changes. The @officialwrc drivers will do this in about 1:15 from buckled in to buckled back in.. we took about 1:45 🤦 With the @yokohamatire ‘s and new @kmcwheels we don’t expect to be changing a tire mid stage.. but still worth the practice.
@subarumotorsportsusa @redbullmotorsports

Who’s ready for the first full season of @nitrorallycross 🙋 Some clips from the first test at @erxmotorpark (round 2 of the championship). Tickets on sale now. Link in bio.

Sept 24/25 Utah Motorsports Campus – Salt Lake City, UT.

Oct 2/3 ERX Motor Park – Minneapolis, MN.

Nov 13/14 Wild Horse Pass Motorsports Park – Phoenix, AZ.

Nov 20/21 Glen Helen Raceway – San Bernadino, CA.

Dec 4/5 The FIRM – Jacksonville, FL.

@yokohamatire @kmcwheels @subarumotorsportsusa @nitrocircus @alpinestars @bellhelmets @kuhl @motul @redbullmotorsports #carsthatfly #tracksthatthrill

node.text: Always wanted to drive a pro 4 truck. Very similar driving style to my @nitrorallycross Subaru which makes the transition seamless. The truck reacts a bit slower because of the weight and suspension but has the power to make up for it. I will be joining @andrewcarlson15 ‘s @redbullmotorsports @yokohamatire team for @crandonoffroad this year in the Pro-4 class. Only got 5 laps of practice.. but that is 5 more than I got last year before showing up at the World Championships in the pro-2 and I’m much more at home with the aggressive driving style of all wheel drive! #kidinacandystore @redbull @alpinestars @carlsonmoto #gameon

node.text: So stoked to see Skate in the Olympics tonight. Big step for the action sports industry. @trevorpiranha @street_bike_tommy @lynzskate and myself just put in the popcorn ready to take a seat and cheer on @jaggereaton .. My old moto trainer Todd Jacobs has been helping him get ready for the Games and said he’s the toughest “kid” he’s ever worked with (he’s worked with @davidbaileymx @jeremymcgrath @r_sipes @prod .. the list goes on and on but that’s a heavy compliment that Todd doesn’t give lightly) Good luck buddy!

node.text:
First test on the second of five @nitrorallycross tracks we are building this year was absolutely awesome! Take a ride with me for a lap at @erxmotorpark if you have a minute. Tickets on sale now (link in bio). Huge thanks to @andrewcarlson15 and the entire @carlsonmoto crew for the hospitality. And a few notes to any potential NRX competitors. the new @kmcwheels were magic.. We were able to run air pressure much lower and never had a single issue.
Whatever bead retention design that KMC have developed is making our lives easy. Also, we made the decision today after a lot of rain.. The @yokohamatire ‘s were designed for more traditional rx courses and I was unsure if we needed to allow the Yokohama Rally AO35 rally tire (which would have taken some work with current rim sizes) but the RallyCross AO54 became more fun to drive as the track conditions got muddier. Happy the weather didn’t cooperate because we were able to test and see that the tire exceeded our expectations. #perfecttestday #builtbydrivers #carsthatfly #tracksthatthrill @subarumotorsportsusa @nitrocircus @alpinestars @redbullmotorsports

node.text:
Spent the week here in Minnesota building the track for round two of the championship. Amazing working with @andrewcarlson15 and crew. The track has so much elevation change, huge banks and zer-gravity drops. It’s windy and going to race really well. Almost no dust and great dirt here but we are intentionally not watering a few of the corners to see if the swept line could be a potential solution for other tracks where the soil blue grooves right away. Happy to get some laps on the CanAm to confirm the jumps are super smooth and will be easy on the cars.
@scott_speed @nitrocircus @yokohamatire @redbullmotorsports
